div.p:
I bleſs God I can with a good conſcience declare to

the World, that I ever deſigned to do good by my Miniſtry according to my mean Capacity; and to that end I have alwayes ſet my ſelf againſt the two great evils of the Age, Diviſion and Debauchery. I have likewiſe made it my buſineſs upon all occaſions to commend the Diſcipline and Methods of the Church of England, as tending more to the promotion of true Holineſs, than any of thoſe Devices which have been formed againſt Her, and which God never proſpered;

and I am ſure the ſame will appear to be my deſign in this Treatiſe, which I humbly offer to you.
